 time pupils of all ages who are sole or dual main registrations.</p></td></tr><tr><td colspan="4"><p>5. Figures are as at January of each given year.</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2015-09-14T14:29:21.74Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417247/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417247/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417247/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-07","Free School Meals: West Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many pupils in the county of West Sussex were eligible for free school meals in each year from 2005-06 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","9188"
