"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417328","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-10","<p>The negotiations over the Sustainable Development Goals were concluded at the UN in August after much international discussion and will now be formally adopted at the UN General Assembly later this month. It is necessary that targets are able to draw on appropriate international measures and the language on premature mortality is consistent with the WHO Global Action Plan on Non-Communicable Diseases (NCDs).</p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2015-09-10T15:20:19.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417328/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417328/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417328/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-07","Developing Countries: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what her policy is on changing the wording of Sustainable Development Goal 3.4 from premature mortality to preventable mortality in order to include people aged over 70 within the scope of the goal; and what discussions she has had with (a) interested parties and (b) her counterparts in other countries on this matter.","false","Biography information for Clive Lewis","Norwich South","Clive Lewis","9144"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417329","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-14","<p>DFID has offset all its air miles flown annually since 2008 through the Government Carbon Offsetting Scheme (GCOF). We have spent the following sums in each of the last three years:</p><p> </p><p>2011/12: £8,345</p><p>2012/13: £14,208</p><p> </p><p>2013/14: £25,341</p><p> </p><p>In 2011/12 and 2012/13 payment was made to EDF Trading Ltd. In 2013/14 it was made to Carbon Footprint Ltd.</p>","Welwyn Hatfield","Grant Shapps",,"2015-09-14T16:39:17.483Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417329/answer","Biography information for Grant Shapps","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417329/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417329/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-07","Department for International Development: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much her Department spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three years; and to which companies payments in respect of carbon offsetting were made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9172"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417330","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-14","<p>Since the 2010-2011 financial year, DFID published evaluations are available on the Department’s external website. No specific evaluation of DFID’s development policies carried out by any commissioned external organisation has been published since the 2010-2011 financial year.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-09-14T16:47:55.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417330/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417330/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417330/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-07","Department for International Development: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what policy evaluations have been carried out by external organisations for her Department and its non-departmental public body in each financial year since 2010-11; whether the output of those evaluations was published; which organisation carried out each such evaluation; and what the value of each contract to provide that evaluation was.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","9253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417331","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-14","<p>During 2013, DFID disbursed £3.9m of Official Development Assistance (ODA) on programmes in the UK which represents 0.04% of total DFID ODA. The funds were spent on development awareness programmes including school partnerships and the development awareness fund.</p>","New Forest West","Mr Desmond Swayne",,"2015-09-14T16:45:25.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417331/answer","Biography information for Sir Desmond Swayne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417331/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417331/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-07","Department for International Development: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much and what proportion of her Department's budget is spent in the UK.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","9085"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417332","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>No decision has been taken to close the magistrates’ courts in Kettering and Corby.</p><p>We will consider all identified impacts once the consultation closes and all responses have been fully analysed. To ensure that access to justice is maintained, even in more rural locations, we are committed to providing alternative ways for users to access our services, including the use of other civic buildings. We are building a justice system which is simpler, swifter and more efficient. By using modern technology we can meet the needs of everyone who uses our services now and in the future.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T13:42:09.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417332/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417332/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417332/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Magistrates' Courts: Northamptonshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate his Department has made of the potential additional (a) travel expenses, (b) costs of non-attendance and (c) other costs to the public purse that would arise due to closure of magistrates courts in (i) Kettering and (ii) Corby.","false","Biography information for Tom Pursglove","Corby","Tom Pursglove","9093"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417333","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-29","<p>I apologise for the delay in responding to the letter sent by right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton in respect of Mr Israr Malik. A response was sent on 9 September providing a full account of the information requested. In addition the response sent provided an explanation for the delay and actions taken to mitigate against any future delay occurring.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-09-29T15:27:53.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417333/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417333/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417333/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Members: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, when he intends to reply to the letter to him dated 21 July 2015 from the right hon. Member for Manchester, Gorton with regard to Israr Hussain Malik.","false","Biography information for Sir Gerald Kaufman","Manchester, Gorton","Sir Gerald Kaufman","9095"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417334","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>Both the Lord Chancellor and I have, and will continue to, engage with a broad range of legal aid providers and representative groups.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T15:29:04.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417334/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417334/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417334/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Legal Aid Scheme: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what representations he has received on the recent reduction in the legal aid budget.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9101"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417335","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>As a directly salaried service, the PDS does not bill for work in the same way as private practice, therefore it is not possible to provide a comparable estimate of cost per hour.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T15:16:01.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417335/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417335/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417335/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Police Stations: Legal Representation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the cost per hour to the Public Defender Service of providing a legal representative in a police station; and what hourly rate is paid for such work under the Legal Aid system.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417336","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p>As a directly salaried service, the PDS does not bill for work in the same way as private practice, therefore it is not possible to provide a comparable estimate of cost per case.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T14:52:59.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417336/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417336/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417336/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Criminal Proceedings: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the cost to the public purse is per case for defendants represented by (a) the Public Defender Service and (b) firms in private practice.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9102"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417337","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-08","<p>The policy evaluations which have been carried out by external organisations for the Ministry of Justice and the National Offender Management Service since 2010/11 are listed in the accompanying table. Information is also provided on whether the output was published, the name of the organisation which carried out the work and the value of the contract.</p><p>The published policy evaluation reports can be found on the GOV.UK website: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=research-and-analysis&amp;topics%5b%5d=all&amp;departments%5b%5d=ministry-of-justice&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5b%5d=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications?keywords=&amp;publication_filter_option=research-and-analysis&amp;topics%5b%5d=all&amp;departments%5b%5d=ministry-of-justice&amp;official_document_status=all&amp;world_locations%5b%5d=all&amp;from_date=&amp;to_date</a></p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-08T13:00:12.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417337/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417337/answer","9254.xls","Costs of Policy Evaluations 2010-2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417337/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Ministry of Justice: Consultants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will list what policy evaluations have been carried out by external organisations for his Department and its agencies in each financial year since 2010-11; whether the output of those evaluations was published; which organisation carried out each such evaluation; and what the value of each contract to provide that evaluation was.","false","Biography information for Chuka Umunna","Streatham","Mr Chuka Umunna","9254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417338","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-09-15","<p /> <p>The data provided in this PQ are taken from a live management information system and can change over time. They are management information and are not subject to the same level of checks as official statistics. Data provided has been extracted specifically to answer this question and has not been cross referenced with case files.</p><p> </p><p>22,562 women had claims accepted in the Employment Tribunals in 14/15. It is not possible to identify how many women within this number were made compulsory redundant, dismissed or were treated in a way that made them leave their job.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is committed to encouraging people to resolve their disputes at the earliest point. Employment tribunals should be the last resort where earlier attempts to resolve workplace disputes have failed.</p><p> </p><p>Early Conciliation was launched in April 2014 and places a requirement on anyone involved in a workplace dispute who is considering an Employment Tribunal claim to contact Acas first. This gives Acas the chance to encourage the parties to resolve their differences through conciliation without the need for an Employment Tribunal claim to be made.</p>","Grantham and Stamford","Nick Boles",,"2015-09-15T14:18:03.68Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417338/answer","Biography information for Nick Boles","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417338/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417338/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-09-07","Employment Tribunals Service: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, how many women who were (a) dismissed, (b) made compulsorily redundant and (c) treated in a way that made them leave their job issued an employment tribunal claim in 2014-15; and what steps he is taking to reduce the incidence of such claims.","false","Biography information for Kate Green","Stretford and Urmston","Kate Green","9219"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417339","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-13","<p>The following table provides details of how much the Ministry of Justice has spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three financial years and the companies to which these payments were made.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Amount spent </strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Company</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>£1,939</p></td><td><p>South Pole</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>£794</p></td><td><p>EDF, South Pole</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>£1,838</p></td><td><p>Carbon Footprint Ltd</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>This has fallen significantly from the £29,804 spent in 2010/11.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-13T11:31:29.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417339/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417339/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417339/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Ministry of Justice: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how much his Department spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three years; and to which companies payments in respect of carbon offsetting were made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9173"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417340","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-21","<p /> <p>In an increasingly digital age, users will not always need to attend hearings in person in order to access the justice system and whilst we have already established alternative ways users can interact with our services, we are looking to expand these provisions to provide more choice than is currently available. For example through making better use of technology, including video conferencing, and exploring whether we can appropriately make use of civic buildings for certain types of hearing.</p><p> </p><p>No decisions will be made until every response to the consultation has been carefully considered.</p><p> </p><p>Comparable travel time data for all courts in Greater Manchester that are not included in the consultation, is provided below. This shows that 99.6% of citizens in Greater Manchester will still be able to reach their court within an hour by car if those courts included in the consultation were to close.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Alexandra House, Manchester Tribunals</strong></p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td><p><strong> Time</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>%</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="5"><p><strong>By Car</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>0-30min</strong></p></td><td><p>52%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>30-60min</strong></p></td><td><p>44%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>60-120min</strong></p></td><td><p>4%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>&gt;120min</strong></p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>no data</strong></p></td><td><p>0%</p></td></tr><tr><td rowspan="5"><p><strong>By Public Transport</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>0-30min</strong></p></td><td><p>7%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>30-60min</strong></p></td><td><p>45%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>60-120min</strong></p></td><td><p>45%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>&gt;120min</strong></p></td><td><p>3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>no data</st