"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417341","Department for Education","false","2015-09-10","<p>The government is fully committed to children’s rights and to implementing the UN Convention on the Rights of the Child (UNCRC). This can be seen through our work to embed children’s rights in government policy, including:</p><p> </p><ul><li><p>strengthening the remit of the Children’s Commissioner in England through the Children and Families Act 2014, giving them a statutory role to promote and protect children’s rights;</p></li><li><p>consulting children on issues that affect them (Article 12 of the UNCRC), including: a group of disabled children who provide regular ‘user perspective’ on how our SEN reforms; and my regular meetings with children in care and care leavers;</p></li><li><p>revising the citizenship programme of study to make clear that schools should develop pupils’ understanding of democracy, government and the rights and responsibilities of citizens.</p></li></ul><p> </p><p>Last year we submitted the UK’s fifth UNCRC periodic review report to the UN Committee on the Rights of the Child, and we will give evidence to that Committee next year.</p><p> </p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-09-10T16:14:23.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417341/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417341/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417341/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-09-07","Children's Rights: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the Government's work to increase awareness of children's human rights.","false","Biography information for Mims Davies","Eastleigh","Mims Davies","9117"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417342","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>HMCTS does not hold this information centrally.</p><p>We will consider all identified impacts once the consultation closes and all responses have been fully analysed.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T15:10:46.207Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417342/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417342/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417342/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Courts: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what costs were paid by HM Courts and Tribunals Service for (a) attendance, (b) travel, (c) loss of earnings, (d) childcare and (e) subsistence for all courts in Greater Manchester in each of the last three years; and what estimate he has made of the likely levels of such costs if his proposals for future courts provision are implemented.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","9113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417343","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-10","<p>On 11 June we announced the start of the post-implementation review of the introduction of fees in the Employment Tribunals. The review will seek to assess the effect fees have had including, so far as possible, any differential impact on people with protected characteristics and the types of case they bring.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-10T16:58:05.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417343/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417343/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417343/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Employment Tribunals Service: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the introduction of employment tribunal fees on access to justice for women subjected to pregnancy-related detriment or dismissal by an employer; and what steps he plans to take to improve access to justice for such women.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","9118"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417344","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-15","<p>The consultation is open until 8 October and we will consider the potential costs in the North West once the consultation closes and all responses have been analysed.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-15T14:26:43.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417344/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417344/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417344/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Administration of Justice: North West","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what estimate he has made of the (a) capital and (b) revenue costs of implementing his proposals for future provision of HM Courts and Tribunal services in the North West.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","9110"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417345","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>This information can be obtained from HMCTS systems but requires collation.</p><p>I will write to the Hon member with this information and place a copy in the library of the House in due course.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T15:24:46.917Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417345/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417345/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417345/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Courts: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the operating costs were of each court in Greater Manchester by type of expenditure in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Ann Coffey","Stockport","Ann Coffey","9111"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417346","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p>Our policy is to implement the new own client and duty contracts on 11 January 2016. This is the best way to ensure a sustainable market for criminal legal aid and deliver value for money for the taxpayer. Sufficient bids have been received for the criminal duty contracts tender to go ahead.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-09-14T15:22:10.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417346/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417346/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417346/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Legal Aid Scheme: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what contingency plans his Department has made for the possibility of all criminal defence firms withdrawing their bids for new legal aid contracts.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9104"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417347","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-10","<p /> <p>Our laws to protect children from sexual abuse and exploitation are rightly robust and are respected across the world. The Government is always receptive to possible improvements in the law but has no plans to reform or review it with regard to the issues set out in the question.</p><p>The nature of the material, age and maturity of children involved in such cases or any evidence of coercion or exploitation would be taken into account by the Crown Prosecution Service when deciding whether to prosecute.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-09-10T14:11:35.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417347/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417347/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417347/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Young People: Internet","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will review and reform legislation on the prosecution of teenagers engaging in consensual sexual relationships over social media and the internet.","false","Biography information for Andy Slaughter","Hammersmith","Andy Slaughter","9327"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417348","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-09-14","<p /> <p>The Government is committed to maintaining a strong response to hate crime, including disability hate crime. There are already tough sentencing options available to the courts for crimes motivated by or demonstrating hostility on the basis of disability. We will keep this area of the law under review. Hate crime is a devolved matter for Northern Ireland.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-09-14T14:45:35.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417348/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417348/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417348/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-09-07","Hate Crime: Disability","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, if he will strengthen the penalties for disability hate crimes.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","9337"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417349","Leader of the House","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Office of the Leader of the House of Commons is part of the Cabinet Office. Our answer is included in the response by the Minister for the Cabinet Office.</p>","Epsom and Ewell","Chris Grayling",,"2015-09-14T15:34:12.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417349/answer","Biography information for Chris Grayling","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417349/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417349/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2015-09-07","Leader of the House of Commons: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, how much his Office spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three years; and to which companies payments in respect of carbon offsetting were made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9174"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417350","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>In the last three years the Northern Ireland Office has spent the following on carbon offsetting:</p><p><strong>2012 </strong></p><p>£1,290 paid to the Environment Agency.</p><p><strong>2013</strong></p><p>£1,290 paid to the Environment Agency and £1,752 paid to the Department of Energy and Climate Change.</p><p><strong>2014 </strong></p><p>£950 paid to the Environment Agency and £3,720 paid to the Department of Energy and Climate Change.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-14T10:07:22.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417350/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417350/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417350/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Northern Ireland Office: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how much her Department spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three years; and to which companies payments in respect of carbon offsetting were made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9175"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417351","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>To date we have not been contacted by any organisation seeking our assistance.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-14T10:09:14.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417351/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417351/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417351/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Refugees: France","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps her Department is taking to assist in the transportation via Cork of donations of clothing and other materials from North Down to refugees stranded in Calais; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","9181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417352","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>On 11 September, I attended the first meeting of the Working Group on Syrian refugees at the Home Office. The Northern Ireland Office will work with the Northern Ireland Executive to ensure that Northern Ireland plays its part in meeting the Government’s aim of resettling vulnerable refugees from Syria and the region.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-14T10:11:59.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417352/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417352/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417352/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what discussions she has had with the First and Deputy First Ministers of Northern Ireland on accepting refugees from UN camps in countries bordering Syria; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","9182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417353","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government is co-operating fully with the Inquiry, including providing full access to review relevant papers.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-14T12:14:56.01Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417353/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417353/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417353/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Kincora Children's Home","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, when the Government papers containing reference to Kincora Boys Home, Belfast that were recently given to the Northern Ireland Historical Abuse Inquiry will be made available for public viewing.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","9341"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417354","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-10","<p>A number of events will be taking place across Northern Ireland, including a special service in St Anne’s Cathedral to mark the occasion of Her Majesty becoming the longest serving monarch in British history. I congratulate Her Majesty on this remarkable achievement. Throughout her long reign Her Majesty has displayed selfless devotion to duty and commitment to all parts of our United Kingdom, including in Northern Ireland.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-10T11:59:27.967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417354/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417354/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417354/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Queen Elizabeth II: Anniversaries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what plans her Department has to celebrate in Northern Ireland Her Majesty Queen Elizabeth II becoming the longest serving British monarch; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","9289"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417355","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>The Government is working through the arrangements. However, we recognise that the increase in numbers will require an expansion of current networks and the impact on local communities and infrastructure will need to be managed carefully.</p><p>We are keen to work with the Northern Ireland Executive to facilitate the settlement of Syrian refugees while ensuring there is an equitable distribution across the country.</p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-14T10:13:50.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417355/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417355/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417355/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what estimate she has made of the number of Syrian refugees who will be accepted by Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","9264"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417356","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-09-14","<p>Clearly, the cost of such a major expansion will be significant. The current Syrian resettlement scheme is funded through a mixture of Official Development Assistance and EU funds. It is the Government’s intention that the expansion of the scheme will be funded in the same way, easing the burden on local communities as we meet the moral obligation to play our part in responding to the refugee crisis in Syria.</p><p>Under existing arrangements, UK resettlement schemes provide 12 months of funding to limit the impact of new arrivals on local authorities and services and to ensure that new arrivals are properly supported and integrated. Beyond that time refugees are treated in the same way as any other UK resident, with access to the labour market and mainstream benefits. This system works well. However, all arrangements will need to be reviewed over the coming weeks given the increase in numbers to ensure fairness, protect local services and the quality of the care provided to refugees.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-09-14T10:18:02.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417356/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417356/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417356/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if she will take steps to ensure additional funding is made available to the Northern Ireland Executive to assist the settlement of Syrian refugees in Northern Ireland over the lifetime of this Parliament; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","9265"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417357","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-09-10","<p>As the Prime Minister stated on 7 September 2015 the police and security services have stopped at least six different attempts to attack the UK in the last 12 months. We cannot comment further on these sensitive operations.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-09-10T16:37:55.51Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417357/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417357/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417357/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-09-07","Terrorism","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Prime Minister's statement of 7 September 2015, how many of the at least six attempted terrorist attacks in the UK within the last 12 months were halted by drone strikes.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","9288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417358","Department for International Development","false","2015-09-14","<p>The UK government has provided funding for UN agencies and NGOs which includes support for Syrian refugees in Italy and in Greece.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The UK is prioritising its aid efforts where the need is greatest. Only a small percentage of Syrians displaced from Syria are seeking asylum in Europe; the vast majority remain in Syria and neighbouring countries. DFID is providing over £1 billion in response to the conflict in Syria. Of this, £501 million is for inside Syria and £519 million is to support neighbouring countries deal with the influx of refugees and pressures this creates, including Lebanon, Jordan and Turkey. This has so far provided more than 18 million food rations, 2.4 million medical consultations and access to clean water for 1.6 million people. By meeting these basic needs we are helping Syrians stay in their home region.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Putney","Justine Greening",,"2015-09-14T16:36:50.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417358/answer","Biography information for Justine Greening","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417358/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417358/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2015-09-07","Syria: Refugees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, if the Government will provide additional aid assistance to EU member states receiving large numbers of refugees from Syria to help them with their humanitarian work.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","9126"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417359","Home Office","false","2015-09-21","<p>The Government has been very clear that will offer practical assistance to Member states under pressure, both bi-laterally and through the European Asylum Support Office (EASO). We believe it is important to help build asylum and border security capacity and capability in other countries so that they are better able to deal with increased demands on their national systems.</p><p>We have already provided more resource – over 1,000 working days - to support missions coordinated by EASO to other Member States, such as Italy and Greece, than any other Member State. We continue to provide bi-lateral support to the Greek asylum system and on assisted voluntary return of illegal migrants.</p><p>We also support the European Commission’s proposals for Hot Spots that will help ensure that migrants are registered and fingerprinted and that refugees are identified and protected quickly, while those with no need of protection can be returned immediately. We will continue to provide resource and expertise to Member States under pressure as and when required.</p>","Watford","Richard Harrington",,"2015-09-21T15:19:39.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417359/answer","Biography information for Richard Harrington","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417359/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417359/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-09-07","Refugees: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will make it her policy to provide administrative assistance to EU member states receiving the highest numbers of Syrian refugees to help them to process asylum claims.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","9109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417360","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-14","<p>We have already supported changes allowing for the expulsion of members for poor conduct and will work to ensure the House of Lords continues to function well by looking, with others, at issues such as the size of the chamber and the retirement of peers.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-09-14T15:47:01.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417360/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417360/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417360/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-07","House of Lords: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what his policy is on reform of the House of Lords.","false","Biography information for Justin Madders","Ellesmere Port and Neston","Justin Madders","9202"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417361","Prime Minister","false","2015-09-11","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the letter of 8 September 2015 from Sir John Chilcot to the Foreign Affairs Committee published on its website.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-09-11T12:58:31.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417361/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417361/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417361/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-09-07","Iraq Committee of Inquiry","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, if he will request information from Sir John Chilcott on (a) how many people have yet to respond to letters sent as part of the Maxwellisation process prior to the finalisation of the report of the Iraq Inquiry and (b) the names of each such person.","false","Biography information for Roger Mullin","Kirkcaldy and Cowdenbeath","Roger Mullin","9089"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417362","Scotland Office","false","2015-09-15","<p>The Scotland Office made no payments in respect of carbon offsetting in each of the last three years.</p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-09-15T15:04:03.31Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417362/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417362/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417362/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-09-07","Scotland Office: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, how much his Department spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three years; and to which companies payments in respect of carbon offsetting were made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9176"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417363","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-15","<p>Our records show the following payments were made:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- In 2012 we paid a total of £6209.26 to RWE Supply and Trading Switzerland SA</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>- In March 2014 we made a payment of £448.02 to EDF Trading.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>We have no other payments recorded on our system since the last payment.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-09-15T10:42:40.803Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417363/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417363/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/417363/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-07","Department for Transport: Carbon Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much his Department spent on carbon offsetting in each of the last three years; and to which companies payments in respect of carbon offsetting were made in each such year.","false","Biography information for Philip Davies","Shipley","Philip Davies","9177"
