"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416338","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-11","<p>On the 31<sup>st</sup> August the total proportion of miles with speed reductions due to roadworks was 10 per cent for the (a) M1, (b) M5, (c) M6, (d) M25, (e) M62 and (f) M4 combined. Roadworks will inevitably arise as part of this Government’s ambitious £15.2bn plan of capital investment to improve the capacity and condition of England’s motorways and major ‘A’ roads which includes a tripling of the annual level of investment on road enhancements by the end of the decade.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-09-11T13:07:52.93Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416338/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416338/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416338/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","Motorways: Repairs and Maintenance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of the total mileage of the (a) M1, (b) M5, (c) M6, (d) M25, (e) M62 and (f) M4 operated (i) without reduced speed restrictions and (ii) at a reduced speed due to roadworks on 31 August 2015.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","8982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416339","Department of Health","false","2015-09-11","<p>This level of information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p>","North East Bedfordshire","Alistair Burt",,"2015-09-11T11:11:19.14Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416339/answer","Biography information for Alistair Burt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416339/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416339/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-09-04","Mental Health Services: Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much each clinical commissioning group spent on (a) all psychological therapies and (b) cognitive behavioural therapy in each year from 2011-12 to 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","8983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416340","Department for Transport","false","2015-09-11","<p>The following sections of the M1 were operating at reduced speed limits on the 31 August 2015 due to roadworks taking place:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p /> <p>M1 J11-12, M1 J15-19, M1 J28-31, M1 J32-35a, and M1 J39-42.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>These roadworks all relate to road upgrades, part of an ambitious £15.2bn plan of capital investment to improve the capacity and condition of England’s motorways and major ‘A’ roads which includes a tripling of the annual level of investment on road enhancements by the end of the decade.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-09-11T13:26:07.11Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416340/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416340/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/416340/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-09-04","M1","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, on which sections of the M1 motorway reduced speed limits were operating because of roadworks taking place or being planned on 31 August 2015.","false","Biography information for Toby Perkins","Chesterfield","Toby Perkins","8984"
